\begin_layout Section
Crystal Lattices
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A 
\series bold
crystal lattice
\series default
 is a periodic array of objects, i.e.
 7's, atoms, molecules ions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each object has identical surroundings.
 Periodicity is generated by translation symmetry operators 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{1,}t_{2},t_{3}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The entire infinite array of objects can be described by giving the structure
 within the unit cell and by giving 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{1,}t_{2},t_{3}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\end_layout

