\begin_layout Standard
A plane light wave of wavelength 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

 traveling to the right with 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

in-phase
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 wave front parallel to the grating produces two coherent circular waves
 emanating from the 2 slits at A and B.
 The two waves will add up in phase at point P on a screen, if the path
 length difference, 
\begin_inset Formula $s=BD$
\end_inset

 , is a multiple of wavelength 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $s=dsin\theta=n\gamma$
\end_inset

 
