\begin_layout Paragraph
Experimental Reflectivity along the (00L) Crystal Truncation Rod (CTR) for
 ferro-electric PZT thin-film capacitor heterostructure
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $PZT=Pb(Zr_{0.3}Ti_{0.7})O_{3}$
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The experimentally measured x-ray reflectivity of the PZT capacitor structure
 taken at 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda=0.914\mathring{A}$
\end_inset

.
 The inset shows the layers within the heteroepitaxial structure, a 
\begin_inset Formula $SrTiO_{3}$
\end_inset

(001) substrate, a 136-nm-thick 
\begin_inset Formula $SruO_{3}$
\end_inset

bottom electrode, a 20-nm-thick PZT film and a 30-nm-thick Ag top electrode.
 The angle positions for the three distinct (001) Bragg peaks mark off the
 the three distinct 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 lattice oncstnats of 
\begin_inset Formula $SrTiO_{3},SrRuO_{3},$
\end_inset

and PZT.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $s_{001}=3.905,3.970,4.130\mathring{A}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The two patterns of oscillation are due to the thickness of the 
\begin_inset Formula $SrRuO_{3}$
\end_inset

and PZT films, the smaller period oscillation belongs to the thicker film.
 The Ag top electrode has a polycrystalline structure and does not measurably
 contribute to the scattered intensity in this high-resolution scan.
 
\end_layout

