\begin_layout Standard
Relationships from classical physics: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $k=\frac{2\pi}{\lambda}=p/\hbar$
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $KE=\hbar\omega-E=\frac{p^{2}}{2m}=\hbar^{2}\frac{k^{2}}{2m}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $k=\frac{\sqrt{2m(\hbar\omega-E)}}{\hbar}$
\end_inset

, or 
\begin_inset Formula $k(\mathring{A})=0.521\sqrt{KE(eV)}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Due to electron delocalization, we can describe the dissociated core photoelectr
on as the spherical wave to describe its trajectory
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\Psi_{out}(\overrightarrow{r})=\frac{\Psi_{0}e^{i\overrightarrow{k}\cdot\overrightarrow{r}}}{r}=\frac{\Psi_{0}e^{ikr}}{r}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

